call again tomorrow. Yes, that'll be all right, I suppose. She may even return tonight.'

'Might I ask you,' I said, 'to tell me more about her?'

'Well, that's easy,' said Madame Lecerf. 'She is quite a good singer, tzigan songs, you know, that kind. She is extraordinarily beautiful. Elle fait des passions.

I like her awfully and I have a room at this flat whenever I say in Paris. Here is her picture, by the way.'

